noninterest revenue is securities/private equity gains, which totaled $1.8billion, up 73% from the
prior year. the increase was a result of net gains in the private equity portfolio of $1.4billion
in 2004, compared with $27million in net gains in 2003. partially offsetting these gains were
lower investment securities gains in treasury.
net interest income was a negative $1.2billion, compared with a negative $177million in the prior
