federal funds purchased represents overnight
funds. securities sold under repurchase agreements
generally mature between one day and three months.
commercial paper generally is issued in amounts not
less than $100,000 and with maturities of 270days
or less. other borrowed funds
consist of demand
notes, term federal funds purchased and various
other borrowings that generally have maturities of
one year or less. at december31, 2004, jpmorgan
chase had no lines of credit for general corporate
purposes.
